{"title":"Heavy mace","url":"https://nethackwiki.com/wiki/Heavy_mace","type":"markdown","data":"| )                |                                                         |\n| ---------------- | ------------------------------------------------------- |\n| Name             | heavy mace                                              |\n| Appearance       | heavy mace                                              |\n| Damage vs. small | 1d10+1                                                  |\n| Damage vs. large | 1d10                                                    |\n| To-hit bonus     | +0                                                      |\n| Weapon skill     | [mace](/wiki/Mace \"Mace\")                               |\n| Size             | [one-handed](/wiki/One-handed \"One-handed\")             |\n| Base price       | 10 [zm](/wiki/Zorkmid \"Zorkmid\") (+10/positive enchant) |\n| Weight           | [50](/wiki/Weight \"Weight\")                             |\n| Material         | [iron](/wiki/Iron \"Iron\")                               |\n\nA **heavy mace** is a type of [weapon](/wiki/Weapon \"Weapon\") that appears in [EvilHack](/wiki/EvilHack \"EvilHack\") and [Hack'EM](/wiki/Hack%27EM \"Hack'EM\"). It is a one-handed weapon that uses the [mace](/wiki/Mace \"Mace\") [skill](/wiki/Skill \"Skill\"), and has a default [object material](/wiki/Object_material \"Object material\") of [iron](/wiki/Iron \"Iron\").\n\nThe heavy mace is the [base item](/wiki/Base_item \"Base item\") for the [artifact weapons](/wiki/Artifact_weapon \"Artifact weapon\") [Demonbane](/wiki/Demonbane \"Demonbane\") and [Disrupter](/wiki/Disrupter \"Disrupter\").\n\n## Generation\n\nIn addition to random generation, heavy maces can be sold in general stores and weapon shops.\n\n[Aligned clerics](/wiki/Aligned_cleric \"Aligned cleric\") that are not [drow](/wiki/Drow_\\(monster_attribute\\) \"Drow (monster attribute)\") have a 1⁄2 chance of [generating with](/wiki/Monster_starting_inventory \"Monster starting inventory\") a heavy mace.\n\n[Angelic beings](/wiki/Angelic_being \"Angelic being\") that generate with weapons have a 1⁄2 chance of generating with a heavy mace. For lawful angelic beings, if Demonbane is lawful (i.e. you are not a non-lawful [priest](/wiki/Priest \"Priest\")), their heavy mace has a chance to be made into Demonbane: this will always happen if the angelic being is a [lord](/wiki/M2_LORD \"M2 LORD\") to their kind, and otherwise occurs with a 1⁄20 chance. If a monster would receive Demonbane but it already exists, it has a 1⁄10 chance of getting a heavy mace with an [object property](/wiki/Object_property \"Object property\"). In either case, the angelic being's mace will be blessed, [erodeproofed](/wiki/Erodeproof \"Erodeproof\") and enchanted from +0 to +3.\n\nA heavy mace can be created at a [forge](/wiki/Forge_\\(dungeon_feature\\) \"Forge (dungeon feature)\") by combining two maces.\n\n- *This page is a **[stub](/wiki/Category:Stubs \"Category:Stubs\")**. Should you wish to do so, you can contribute by [**expanding this page**.](https://nethackwiki.com/index.php?title=Heavy_mace\\&action=edit)*\n","html":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html class=\"client-nojs\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\"/>\n<title>Heavy mace - NetHack Wiki</title>\n<script>document.documentElement.className = document.documentElement.className.replace( /(^|\\s)client-nojs(\\s|$)/, \"$1client-js$2\" );</script>\n<script>(window.RLQ=window.RLQ||[]).push(function(){mw.config.set({\"wgCanonicalNamespace\":\"\",\"wgCanonicalSpecialPageName\":false,\"wgNamespaceNumber\":0,\"wgPageName\":\"Heavy_mace\",\"wgTitle\":\"Heavy mace\",\"wgCurRevisionId\":163682,\"wgRevisionId\":163682,\"wgArticleId\":39600,\"wgIsArticle\":true,\"wgIsRedirect\":false,\"wgAction\":\"view\",\"wgUserName\":null,\"wgUserGroups\":[\"*\"],\"wgCategories\":[\"Stubs\",\"EvilHack weapons\",\"Hack'EM weapons\"],\"wgBreakFrames\":false,\"wgPageContentLanguage\":\"en\",\"wgPag