ad.php?debug=false&amp;lang=en&amp;modules=site.styles&amp;only=styles&amp;skin=vector\"/>\n<meta name=\"generator\" content=\"MediaWiki 1.32.5\"/>\n<meta name=\"description\" content=\"A heavy mace is a type of weapon that appears in EvilHack and Hack&#039;EM. It is a one-handed weapon that uses the mace skill, and has a default object material of iron.\"/>\n<link rel=\"image_src\" href=\"/images/6/65/Nethackwiki-logo.png\"/>\n<link rel=\"shortcut icon\" href=\"/images/6/64/Favicon.ico\"/>\n<link rel=\"search\" type=\"application/opensearchdescription+xml\" href=\"/opensearch_desc.php\" title=\"NetHackWiki\"/>\n<link rel=\"EditURI\" type=\"application/rsd+xml\" href=\"https://nethackwiki.com/api.php?action=rsd\"/>\n<link rel=\"canonical\" href=\"/wiki/Heavy_mace\"/>\n<!--[if lt IE 9]><script src=\"/load.php?debug=false&amp;lang=en&amp;modules=html5shiv&amp;only=scripts&amp;skin=vector&amp;sync=1\"></script><![endif]-->\n</head>\n<body class=\"mediawiki ltr sitedir-ltr mw-hide-empty-elt ns-0 ns-subject page-Heavy_mace rootpage-Heavy_mace skin-vector action-view\">\t\t<div id=\"mw-page-base\" class=\"noprint\"></div>\n\t\t<div id=\"mw-head-base\" class=\"noprint\"></div>\n\t\t<div id=\"content\" class=\"mw-body\" role=\"main\">\n\t\t\t<a id=\"top\"></a>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"mw-indicators mw-body-content\">\n</div>\n<h1 id=\"firstHeading\" class=\"firstHeading\" lang=\"en\">Heavy mace</h1>\t\t\t<div id=\"bodyContent\" class=\"mw-body-content\">\n\t\t\t\t<div id=\"siteSub\" class=\"noprint\">From NetHackWiki</div>\t\t\t\t<div id=\"contentSub\"></div>\n\t\t\t\t<div id=\"jump-to-nav\"></div>\t\t\t\t<a class=\"mw-jump-link\" href=\"#mw-head\">Jump to navigation</a>\n\t\t\t\t<a class=\"mw-jump-link\" href=\"#p-search\">Jump to search</a>\n\t\t\t\t<div id=\"mw-content-text\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\" class=\"mw-content-ltr\"><div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\">\n<table class=\"prettytable\" style=\"margin: 0;\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<th colspan=\"2\"><span class=\"nhsym clr-cyan\">)</span>\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Name\n</th>\n<td>heavy mace\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Appearance\n</th>\n<td>heavy mace\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Damage vs. small\n</th>\n<td>1d10+1\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Damage vs. large\n</th>\n<td>1d10\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th>To-hit bonus\n</th>\n<td>+0\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Weapon skill\n</th>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Mace\" title=\"Mace\">mace</a>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Size\n</th>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/One-handed\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"One-handed\">one-handed</a>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Base price\n</th>\n<td>10 <a href=\"/wiki/Zorkmid\" title=\"Zorkmid\">zm</a><br />(+10/positive <br />enchant)\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Weight\n</th>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Weight\" title=\"Weight\">50</a>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Material\n</th>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Iron\" title=\"Iron\">iron</a>\n</td></tr></tbody></table>\n</div>\n<p>A <b>heavy mace</b> is a type of <a href=\"/wiki/Weapon\" title=\"Weapon\">weapon</a> that appears in <a href=\"/wiki/EvilHack\" title=\"EvilHack\">EvilHack</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Hack%27EM\" title=\"Hack&#39;EM\">Hack'EM</a>. It is a one-handed weapon that uses the <a href=\"/wiki/Mace\" title=\"Mace\">mace</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Skill\" title=\"Skill\">skill</a>, and has a default <a href=\"/wiki/Object_material\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Object material\">object material</a> of <a href=\"/wiki/Iron\" title=\"Iron\">iron</a>.\n</p><p>The heavy mace is the <a href=\"/wiki/Base_item\" title=\"Base item\">base item</a> for the <a href=\"/wiki/Artifact_weapon\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Artifact weapon\">artifact weapons</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Demonbane\" title=\"Demonbane\">Demonbane</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Disrupter\" title=\"Disrupter\">Disrupter</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Generation\">Generation</span></h2>\n<p>In addition to random generation, heavy maces can be sold in general stores and weapon shops.\n</p><p><a href=\"/wiki/Aligned_cleric\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Aligned cleric\">Aligned clerics</a> that are not <a href=\"/wiki/Drow_(monster_attribute)\" title=\"Drow (monster attribute)\">drow</a> have a <sup>1</sup>&#8260;<sub>2</sub> chance of <a href=\"/wiki/Monster_starting_inventory\" title=\"Monster starting inventory\">generating with</a> a heavy mace.\n</p><p><a href=\"/wiki/Angelic_being\" title=\"Angelic being\">Angelic beings</a> that generate with weapons have a <sup>1</sup>&#8260;<sub>2</sub> chance of generating with a heavy mace. For lawful angelic beings, if Demonbane is lawful (i.e. you are not a non-lawful <a href=\"/wiki/Priest\" title=\"Priest\">priest</a>), their heavy mace has a chance to be made into Demonbane: this will always happen if the angelic being is a <a href=\"/wiki/M2_LORD\" title=\"M2 LORD\">lord</a> to their kind, and otherwise occurs with a <sup>1</sup>&#8260;<sub>20</sub> chance. If a monster would receive Demonbane but it already exists, it has a <sup>1</sup>&#8260;<sub>10</sub> chance of getting a heavy mace with an <a href=\"/wiki/Object_property\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Object property\">object property</a>. In either case, the angelic being's mace will be blessed, <a href=\"/wiki/Erodeproof\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Erodeproof\">erodeproofed</a> and enchanted from +0 to +3.\n</p><p>A heavy mace can be created at a <a href=\"/wiki/Forge_(dungeon_feature)\" title=\"Forge (dungeon feature)\">forge</a> by combining two maces.\n</p>\n<div class=\"stub\">\n<dl><dd><i>This page is a <b><a href=\"/wiki/Category:Stubs\" title=\"Category:Stubs\">stub</a></b>. Should you wish to do so, you can contribute by <a class=\"external text\" href=\"https://nethackwiki.com/index.php?title=Heavy_mace&amp;action=edit\"><b>expanding this page</b>.</a></i></dd></dl>\n</div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20240926184003\nCache expiry: 604800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.012 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.015 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 121/1000000\nPreproc