l id=\"footer-icons\" class=\"noprint\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<li id=\"footer-poweredbyico\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"//www.mediawiki.org/\"><img src=\"/resources/assets/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png\" alt=\"Powered by MediaWiki\" srcset=\"/resources/assets/poweredby_mediawiki_132x47.png 1.5x, /resources/assets/poweredby_mediawiki_176x62.png 2x\" width=\"88\" height=\"31\"/></a>\t\t\t\t\t</li>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div style=\"clear: both;\"></div>\n\t\t</div>\n\t\t\n<script>(window.RLQ=window.RLQ||[]).push(function(){mw.config.set({\"wgPageParseReport\":{\"limitreport\":{\"cputime\":\"0.012\",\"walltime\":\"0.015\",\"ppvisitednodes\":{\"value\":121,\"limit\":1000000},\"ppgeneratednodes\":{\"value\":601,\"limit\":1000000},\"postexpandincludesize\":{\"value\":1378,\"limit\":2097152},\"templateargumentsize\":{\"value\":67,\"limit\":2097152},\"expansiondepth\":{\"value\":6,\"limit\":40},\"expensivefunctioncount\":{\"value\":0,\"limit\":100},\"unstrip-depth\":{\"value\":0,\"limit\":20},\"unstrip-size\":{\"value\":2,\"limit\":5000000},\"timingprofile\":[\"100.00%    8.756      1 -total\",\" 52.58%    4.604      1 Template:Weapon\",\" 29.59%    2.591      1 Template:Metal_color\",\" 24.17%    2.116      4 Template:Frac\",\" 17.39%    1.523      1 Template:Stub\",\" 14.32%    1.254      1 Template:Cyan\"]},\"cachereport\":{\"timestamp\":\"20240926184003\",\"ttl\":604800,\"transientcontent\":false}}});mw.config.set({\"wgBackendResponseTime\":59});});</script>\n\t</body>\n</html>\n","rawPage":"{{weapon\n |color=metal color\n |tile=\n |name=heavy mace\n |smalldmg=1d10+1\n |largedmg=1d10\n |skill=mace\n |cost=10\n |weight=50\n |material=iron\n}}\n\nA '''heavy mace''' is a type of [[weapon]] that appears in [[EvilHack]] and [[Hack'EM]]. It is a one-handed weapon that uses the [[mace]] [[skill]], and has a default [[object material]] of [[iron]].\n\nThe heavy mace is the [[base item]] for the [[artifact weapon]]s [[Demonbane]] and [[Disrupter]].\n\n==Generation==\nIn addition to random generation, heavy maces can be sold in general stores and weapon shops.\n\n[[Aligned cleric]]s that are not [[Drow (monster attribute)|drow]] have a {{frac|2}} chance of [[Monster starting inventory|generating with]] a heavy mace.\n\n[[Angelic being]]s that generate with weapons have a {{frac|2}} chance of generating with a heavy mace. For lawful angelic beings, if Demonbane is lawful (i.e. you are not a non-lawful [[priest]]), their heavy mace has a chance to be made into Demonbane: this will always happen if the angelic being is a [[M2_LORD|lord]] to their kind, and otherwise occurs with a {{frac|20}} chance. If a monster would receive Demonbane but it already exists, it has a {{frac|10}} chance of getting a heavy mace with an [[object property]]. In either case, the angelic being's mace will be blessed, [[erodeproof]]ed and enchanted from +0 to +3.\n\nA heavy mace can be created at a [[Forge (dungeon feature)|forge]] by combining two maces.\n{{stub}}<!--{{variant-36X}}-->\n[[Category:EvilHack weapons]]\n[[Category:Hack'EM weapons]]"}